  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Should we remove the configurability of `--service-account-api-audiences` and use a const such as `https://kubernetes.default.svc`?\r\n\r\nThis allows us to easily extend TokenReview to support validation of arbitrary audiences and would provide a portable name kube API name across clusters to use as part of authentication. However, it would restrict the flexibility of deployments where the service account issuer spans multiple clusters. I'm not sure if people are or should be doing this today.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, we can always append a static `https://kubernetes.default.svc` to the list of implicit API audiences and allow extra API audiences to restrict the scope of tokens in deployments where the service account issuer is shared. This approach would also work with TokenReview.\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-auth-api-reviews \r\n@liggitt ",
